    <!-- Project Modals -->
    <div id="project-modal-styles">
      <!-- Rockfish Modal -->
      <div class="modal fade" id="rockfishModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="projectLabel">
        <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
          <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
              <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
              <h5 class="modal-title" id="rockfishModalLabel">UX Designer - Rockfish Digital - 2017</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
              <h3>Branding Content with Structure, Design, and Usability</h3>

              <p>For the Rockfish Digital's UX team, I developed content solutions with research, analysis, and site mapping and articulated the solutions with wireframes. The complex network of wireframes would satisfy a national client's need to enhance their brand and promote veterinarian data and research to students and professionals.</p>

              <h5>PROBLEM</h5>
              <p>With a complex amount of content and a short deadline, the design project had 3 obstacles:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Structure the content types so that CMS editors can easily manage, update, and create effective content,</li>
                <li>Design the web content so that the client meets their marketing goals of enhancing their brand, and</li>
                <li>Facilitate the navigation, searchability, and findability of content by designing the wireframes in consideration of prominent usability practices.</li>
              </ul>
              <h5>SOLUTION</h5>
              <p>Collaborating with the content strategist and UX lead, we examined the information architecture and client needs. To design the solution, I researched the brand, used affinity diagramming to create site maps, and with Sketch, developed a system of wireframes that were organized and cataloged by navigation and hierarchy.</p>
              <h5>OUTCOME</h5>
              <p>With a design goal of facilitating an efficient IA and proper usability, the wireframes complied with the needs of content editors, users, and the brand by including 8 unique templates that would satisfy a breadth of content with a consistent structure and design. Extra attention was given to user interactions such as browsing content, searching for content, filtering searches, and discovering new content.</p>
              <%= image_tag('rockfish-wires.png', :class=>'img-responsive') %>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
              <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Harman Modal -->
    <div class="modal fade" id="harmanModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="projectLabel">
      <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
        <div class="modal-content">
          <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
            <h5 class="modal-title" id="harmanModalLabel">UX Researcher - Harman International - 2017</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-body">
            <h3>Closing the Gaps on User Research with Collaboration Technologies</h3>
            <p>For Harman's UX team, I guided a groundbreaking research project that analyzed the use of software in the implementation of AV&amp;C networks within consumer and business infrastructures. The extensive research project comprised a global team of collaborators, project stakeholders, and research participants.</p>
            <h5>PROBLEM</h5>
            <p>The complex and technical research project had obstacles to communication and collaboration with the widespread locations of collaborators, stakeholders, and participants.</p>
            <h5>SOLUTION</h5>
            <p>At the central point of research in Dallas, Texas, I successfully implemented and managed the use of cloud-based technologies both as a central space to facilitate research and as a collaboration tool for producing user research deliverables.</p>
            <%= image_tag('cloud-software.png', :class=>'img-responsive') %>
            <h5>OUTCOME</h5>
            <p>As app platforms such as Trello, G Suite, and Slack became central points of consensus, debate, synthesis, insight, organization, and production, the research project reached a new depth with its continuous engagement. The digital collaboration resulted in a fruitful meeting of the minds in a real-world design mapping workshop.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-footer">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
      <!-- Dart Modal -->
    <div class="modal fade" id="dartModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="projectLabel">
      <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
        <div class="modal-content">
          <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
            <h5 class="modal-title" id="dartModalLabel">UX Designer - DART - 2017</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-body">
            <h3>Using Mobile Heuristics to Facilitate User Flow Design</h3>
            <p>For the marketing team at DART, I consulted on the design of a mobile app. Working with wireframes initially created by a development team in Denmark, I had a two weeks to analyze the structure, flow, and design of the app and develop recommendations for the next iteration.</p>
            <h5>PROBLEM</h5>
            <p>With the marketing team's concern with the current state of the app's design, the project had 3 obstacles:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>The UI did not reflect the structure and design of contemporary apps,</li>
              <li>The design and copy did not capture the brand identity, and</li>
              <li>The user flows such as registration and payment were neither concise or clear.</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>SOLUTION</h5>
            <p>With a short amount of time, I relied on UX tools and strategies to provide design and user flow recommendations. To develop recommendations I relied on mobile heuristics, which were developed with research and testing. With a criteria focused on the mobile app environment, I was able to pinpoint the problem areas in usablity and develop recommendations that would improve the existing user flows. With a competitive analysis, I was able to design recommendations that would improve the UI and match the style of the DART brand.</p>
            <%= image_tag('dart-train.png', :class=>'img-responsive') %>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-footer">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
      <!-- Memorial Hermann Modal -->
    <div class="modal fade" id="memorialModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="projectLabel">
