            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
            <h5 class="modal-title" id="memorialModalLabel">Web Designer - Memorial Hermann - 2016-2017</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-body">
            <h3>Designing with Empathy</h3>
            <p>For the digital marketing team at Memorial Hermann, the largest not-for-profit healthcare system in Texas, I developed wireframes for a site that would facilitate prescription fullfillment of specialty pharmaceuticals. The high profile site would need to build trust with patients with chronic conditions who would use the site to fulfill high-cost prescriptions.</p>
            <h5>PROBLEM</h5>
            <p>As a new online campaign for the Specialty Pharmacy department, the design project had the following goals:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Build trust with patients so they would use the site to manage refills,</li>
              <li>Design the navigation so that patients could easily find information about the pharmacy's services, and</li>
              <li>Provide a better designed site compared to other specialty pharmacy sites.</li>
            </ul>
            <h5>SOLUTION</h5>
            <p>To understand the perspective of specialty pharmacy patients, personas were created to point out the common goals and frustrations of these patients who needed to refill prescriptions. The personas and research process brought me to empathize with the patient early on in the design of the site. With this empathetic grasp of the patient's perspective, key strategies were developed to both build trust and convey information to the patient.</p>
            <%= image_tag('pharmacy-wire.png', :class=>'img-responsive') %>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-footer">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
